The article is a readout of a phone call between President Obama and King Salman of Saudi Arabia. The President offered his condolences on the passing of Prince Saud al-Faisal and shared details of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) regarding Iran's nuclear program. The President emphasized that the JCPOA will prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon while ensuring the peaceful nature of their nuclear program. He also reiterated the United States' commitment to working with Gulf partners to counter Iran's destabilizing activities and promote stability in the region. The President and the King also discussed the importance of stopping the fighting in Yemen and ensuring humanitarian assistance reaches all sides of the conflict.